# IntelliJ HTTP Client examples for technical-interview-demo
# This app does not issue JWTs and does not accept Authorization: Bearer tokens.
# Protected app requests use the GitHub OAuth login flow plus the
# technical-interview-demo-session cookie created by Spring Session.
#
# The GitHub token exchange examples below are for diagnostics only.
# GitHub returns an access token for GitHub APIs, not a JWT for this app,
# and the app will not accept that token on /api/**.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
#@sessionCookie = paste-technical-interview-demo-session-here
#@githubClientId = paste-github-client-id-here
#@githubClientSecret = paste-github-client-secret-here
#@githubAuthCode = paste-github-auth-code-here
#@githubAccessToken = paste-github-access-token-here

### App authentication - start GitHub OAuth login flow in a browser-capable client
GET {{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/github

### App authentication - verify the authenticated app session cookie
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
Accept: application/json
